record_data.record_plain_text: OHIO POWER PARTNERS, LLC Interim Rate Schedule for Reactive Supply and Voltage Control from Generation Sources Service Ohio Power Partners, LLC ("Ohio Power") provides Reactive Supply and Voltage Control from Generation Sources Service ("Reactive Power Service") from generating facilities located within the Duke Energy Ohio, Inc. ("Duke Ohio") Zone of the control area administered by the PJM Interconnection, L.L.C. ("PJM") in order to assist in maintaining transmission voltages within acceptable limits on the PJM transmission system. This rate schedule sets forth Ohio Power's revenue requirements for the provision of Reactive Power Service, as contemplated by the revised Schedule 2 of the PJM Open Access Transmission Tariff which provides that PJM will pay generation owners for their monthly revenue requirement for Reactive Power Service. This Rate Schedule shall be effective upon the date authorized by the Federal Energy Regulatory Commission. MONTHLY REVENUE REQUIREMENT: The total Reactive Power Annual Revenue Requirement is $1,300,000.00 The total monthly charge to PJM is $108,333.33
